Our Mission

   The United States Bankruptcy Court of the District of South Dakota
   exists to fulfill Article I, Section 8, Clause 4 of the United States
   Constitution and Title 11 of the United States Code.  The Court's
   essential functions are to adjudicate disputes in a professional manner
   under the applicable statutes and federal and local rules; to maintain
   accurate files and records, to provide case information to the Bar, pro
   se litigants, and the public; and to provide statistical information to
   the public and the Administrative Office of the United States Courts.


